race.comment: PLAY ON WORDS (5) ran a big race on speed last time when fourth over a mile at Tatura. This is easier and off the low draw will take catching this circuit. ESKIMO (1) was safely held in tougher company last time. The start prior was an on speed winner in similar grade to this. Has a big weight but has the rails draw and will take catching. THE BANTAM (3) was solid in richer company last time and the start prior good at Tatura in this class. Nicely placed here and gets a chance to atone. SURELY SPECIAL (6) ran a big race at odds last time over 1600m at Swan Hill when runner-up. Low draw and will give a sight again.
